Commuters plying the Lamu-Witu-Garsen route on Monday experienced an unusual delay, just a day after police officers repulsed an attack by suspected Al-Shabaab militants in Nyongoro.
The heavily armed terrorists ambushed the Border Patrol Unit (BPU) Toyota Land Cruiser which was escorting a convoy of buses from Lamu heading to Gamba and Mombasa at around 11.15am on Sunday.



