A shootout ensued between the more than 10 officers aboard the police vehicle and the militants and lasted for over 10 minutes before the terrorists were overpowered and fled to the bush.
Speaking to the Nation on Monday, bus drivers, conductors and passengers complained that they were forced to stay for hours at the Kibaoni and Witu road blocks before they were allowed to proceed with their journeys.
"This is abnormal. We're used to waiting for one another for less than 30 minutes so that we can travel in one convoy. But today, we've waited for too long. I suspect all this is because of the attempted Al-Shabaab attack at Nyongoro on Sunday," said Hassan Said, a driver.



